302 в”‚ lru 0.12.5 registry+https://github.com/rust-lang/crates.io-index
    в”‚ в”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ unsound advisory detected
    в”‚
    в”њ ID: RUSTSEC-2026-0002
    в”њ Advisory: https://rustsec.org/advisories/RUSTSEC-2026-0002
    в”њ Affected versions of this crate contain a soundness issue in the `IterMut`
      iterator implementation. The `IterMut::next` and `IterMut::next_back`
      methods temporarily create an exclusive reference to the key when
      dereferencing the internal node pointer.
      
      This invalidates the shared pointer held by the internal `HashMap`,
      violating Stacked Borrows rules.
    в”њ Announcement: https://github.com/jeromefroe/lru-rs/pull/224
    в”њ Solution: Upgrade to >=0.16.3 (try `cargo update -p lru`)
